title: Mitch Krenk
content:
Mitchell James Krenk (born November 19, 1959) is a former American football tight end for the Chicago Bears of the NFL. He earned a Super Bowl ring for spending the 1985 Bears season on injured reserve.[1][2]

He attended University of Nebraska.[3]
